From Guy Kuo Subject Re Half page hand scanners The Logitech ScanMan is a nice unit, compact and effective it will bring in graphics with surprisingly good quality Note that its effective resolution in grey scale mode is only about dpi If you don't intend to magnify a graphic, it works fine A true level gray scanner would work better for images I've seen the ScanMan go for as little as used It is a reasonable buy at that price Higher end hand scanners are almost as expensive as used flat bed scanners Here is Seattle, the paper shows occasional good bargains in the classifieds Used color flat beds have been seen as lows as lately Grey scale flatbeds come in around